{"title_page": "Minchumina Airport", "text_new": "{{Infobox airport \n| name         = Minchumina Airport\n| nativename   = Lake Minchumina Airport\n| image        = \n| IATA         = LMA<ref name=\"IATAsearch\">{{cite web|url=http://www.iata.org/publications/Pages/code-search.aspx|title=Airline and Airport Code Search| publisher=[[International Air Transport Association|IATA]]|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n| ICAO         = PAMH\n| FAA          = MHM\n| type         = Public\n| owner        = [[State of Alaska DOT&PF]]\n| operator     = \n| city-served  = [[Lake Minchumina, Alaska]]\n| location     = <!--if different than above-->\n| elevation-f  = 682\n| website      = \n| coordinates  = {{coord|63|53|10|N|152|18|07|W|region:US-AK|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map            = USA Alaska\n| pushpin_relief         = yes\n| pushpin_mapsize        = 250\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of airport in Alaska\n| pushpin_label          = '''LMA'''\n| pushpin_label_position = right\n| r1-number    = 3/21\n| r1-length-f  = 4,184\n| r1-surface   = Gravel\n| stat-year    = 2009\n| stat1-header = Aircraft operations\n| stat1-data   = 1,140\n| stat2-header = Based aircraft\n| stat2-data   = 2\n| footnotes    = Source: [[Federal Aviation Administration]]<ref name=\"FAA\">{{FAA-airport|ID=MHM|use=PU|own=PU|site=50497.*A}}. Federal Aviation Administration. effective April 5, 2012.</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Minchumina Airport''' {{airport codes|LMA<ref name=\"IATAsearch\"/>|PAMH|MHM}} is a state-owned public-use [[airport]] serving [[Lake Minchumina, Alaska|Lake Minchumina]],<ref name=\"FAA\" /> in the [[Yukon-Koyukuk Census Area, Alaska|Yukon-Koyukuk Census Area]] of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Alaska]]. It is also known as '''Lake Minchumina Airport'''.<ref>{{ASN|LMA|LMA - Lake Minchumina Airport}}</ref><ref>{{GCM|LMA|LMA - Lake Minchumina, Alaska}}</ref> In the past, the airport used '''MHM''' IATA code.\n\nScheduled passenger service at this airport is subsidized by the [[United States Department of Transportation]] via the [[Essential Air Service]] program.\n\n== Facilities and aircraft ==\nMinchumina Airport covers an area of {{convert|674|acre|ha|lk=on}} at an [[elevation]] of 678 feet (207 m) above [[mean sea level]]. It has one [[runway]] designated 3/21 with a [[gravel]] surface measuring 4,200 by 100 feet (1,280 x 30 m). For the 12-month period ending December 31, 2005, the airport had 1,140 aircraft operations, an average of 95 per month: 96% [[general aviation]] and 4% [[air taxi]].<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\n== Airlines and destinations ==\nThe following [[airline]] offers scheduled passenger service:\n{{Airport destination list\n| [[Wright Air Service]] | [[Fairbanks International Airport|Fairbanks]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wrightairservice.com/#passengers | title = Flight Schedule | publisher = Wright Air Service | accessdate = June 15, 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Statistics===\n{{Bar graph\n| title = Carrier shares: January \u2013 December 2013<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\" />\n| bar_width   = 26\n| width_units = em\n| label_type  = Carrier&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| data_type   = Passengers (arriving and departing)\n|\n| label1   = [[Wright Air Service|Wright]]\n| data1    = 220\n| comment1 = 99.55%\n|\n| label2   = [[Tanana Air Service|Tanana]]\n| data2    = 1\n| comment2 = 0.45%\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Top domestic destinations: Jan. \u2013 Dec. 2013<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\">\n  {{cite web\n  | url = http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=LMA&End_YearMonth=24168\n  | title = Lake Minchumina, AK: Lake Minchumina Airport (LMA)\n  | publisher = [[Bureau of Transportation Statistics]] (BTS), [[Research and Innovative Technology Administration]] (RITA), [[U.S. Department of Transportation]]\n  | date = December 2013 | accessdate = June 25, 2014\n  }}\n</ref><!--NOTE: source does not list airlines associated with destinations at the time-->\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n! rowspan=\"2\" | City\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Airport name & IATA code\n! colspan=\"2\" | Passengers\n|-\n! 2013\n! 2012\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Fairbanks, Alaska]]\n| [[Fairbanks International Airport|Fairbanks International (FAI)]]\n| align=\"right\" | 100\n| align=\"right\" | 90\n|-\n| 2\n| [[McGrath, AK]]\n| [[McGrath Airport|McGrath Airport (MCG)]]\n| align=\"right\" | &lt;10\n| align=\"right\" | &lt;10\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Other sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* Essential Air Service documents ([http://www.regulations.gov/#!docketDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237 Docket DOT-OST-2008-0237]) from the [[U.S. Department of Transportation]]:\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0001 Ninety-Day Notice (July 29, 2008]: of [[Tatonduk Outfitters]] Limited d/b/a [[Everts Air Alaska]] intent to terminate subsidy-free air service between Fairbanks, and Lake Minchumina, Alaska.\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0002 Order 2008-8-3 (August 6, 2008)]: prohibiting Tatonduk Outfitters, Ltd., d/b/a Everts Air Alaska, from suspending service at Lake Minchumina, Alaska, and requesting proposals by August 22 from carriers interested in providing replacement essential air service (EAS).\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!docketDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237 Order 2008-9-21 (September 16, 2008)]: Selecting Tatonduk Outfitters, Ltd. d/b/a Everts Air Cargo, to provide subsidized essential air service at Lake Minchumina, Alaska, for the two-year period from October 27, 2008, through October 31, 2010, at an annual rate of $42,560.\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0021 Order 2010-7-14 (July 16, 2010)]: selecting [[Warbelow's Air Ventures]], Inc., to provide essential air service (EAS) at Lake Minchumina, Alaska, at an annual subsidy rate of $62,400. The selection extends from November 1, 2010, through October 31, 2012.\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0022 Order 2010-7-20 (July 27, 2010)]: grants Lake Minchumina's Petition for Reconsideration of Order 2010-7-14 and rescinds Order 2010-7-14 selecting Warbelow's Air Ventures, Inc. On reconsideration, we select [[Wright Air Service]], Inc., Option 2, for $93,080 annual subsidy, to provide essential air service (EAS) to Lake Minchumina, Alaska.\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0023 Memorandum (August 3, 2010)]: The startup date for Wright Air Service in Order 2010-7-20 should be November 1, 2010, not October 1, 2010. Wright's contract will run for two years, through October 31, 2012.\n** [http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237-0028 Order 2012-10-14 (October 11, 2012)]: re-selecting Wright Air Service, Inc., to provide Essential Air Service (EAS) at Lake Minchumina, Alaska, for $102,300 annually for two nonstop round trips per week to Fairbanks \u2013 one with a 9-seat IFR Certified aircraft ([[Cessna 208]] or [[Piper Navajo]]) and one with 4-seat single-engine piston aircraft ([[Cessna 206]] or [[Beech Bonanza]]) \u2013 through October 31, 2014.\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050119193439/http://www.alaska.faa.gov/fai/images/ARPT_DIAGRAMS/MHM.gif Alaska FAA airport diagram] <small>([[GIF]])</small>\n* {{FAA-procedures|MHM}}\n{{US-airport2|MHM|PAMH}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in the Yukon\u2013Koyukuk Census Area, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Essential Air Service]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox airport \n| name         = Minchumina Airport\n| nativename   = Lake Minchumina Airport\n| image        = \n| IATA         = LMA<ref name=\"IATAsearch\">{{cite web|url=http://www.iata.org/publications/Pages/code-search.aspx|title=Airline and Airport Code Search| publisher=[[International Air Transport Association|IATA]]|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n| ICAO         = PAMH\n| FAA          = MHM\n| type         = Public\n| owner        = [[State of Alaska DOT&PF]]\n| operator     = \n| city-served  = [[Lake Minchumina, Alaska]]\n| location     = <!--if different than above-->\n| elevation-f  = 682\n| website      = \n| coordinates  = {{coord|63|53|10|N|152|18|07|W|region:US-AK|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map            = USA Alaska\n| pushpin_relief         = yes\n| pushpin_mapsize        = 250\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of airport in Alaska\n| pushpin_label          = '''LMA'''\n| pushpin_label_position = right\n| r1-number    = 3/21\n| r1-length-f  = 4,184\n| r1-surface   = Gravel\n| stat-year    = 2009\n| stat1-header = Aircraft operations\n| stat1-data   = 1,140\n| stat2-header = Based aircraft\n| stat2-data   = 2\n| footnotes    = Source: [[Federal Aviation Administration]]<ref name=\"FAA\">{{FAA-airport|ID=MHM|use=PU|own=PU|site=50497.*A}}. Federal Aviation Administration. effective April 5, 2012.</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Minchumina Airport''' {{airport codes|LMA<ref name=\"IATAsearch\"/>|PAMH|MHM}} is a state owned, public use [[airport]] serving [[Lake Minchumina, Alaska|Lake Minchumina]],<ref name=\"FAA\" /> in the [[Yukon-Koyukuk Census Area, Alaska|Yukon-Koyukuk Census Area]] of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Alaska]]. It is also known as '''Lake Minchumina Airport'''.<ref>{{ASN|LMA|LMA - Lake Minchumina Airport}}</ref><ref>{{GCM|LMA|LMA - Lake Minchumina, Alaska}}</ref> In the past, the airport used '''MHM''' IATA code.\n\nScheduled passenger service at this airport is subsidized by the [[United States Department of Transportation]] via the [[Essential Air Service]] program.\n\n== Facilities and aircraft ==\nMinchumina Airport covers an area of {{convert|674|acre|ha|lk=on}} at an [[elevation]] of 678 feet (207 m) above [[mean sea level]]. It has one [[runway]] designated 3/21 with a [[gravel]] surface measuring 4,200 by 100 feet (1,280 x 30 m). For the 12-month period ending December 31, 2005, the airport had 1,140 aircraft operations, an average of 95 per month: 96% [[general aviation]] and 4% [[air taxi]].<ref name=\"FAA\" />\n\n== Airlines and destinations ==\nThe following [[airline]] offers scheduled passenger service:\n{{Airport destination list\n| [[Wright Air Service]] | [[Fairbanks International Airport|Fairbanks]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wrightairservice.com/#passengers | title = Flight Schedule | publisher = Wright Air Service | accessdate = June 15, 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Statistics===\n{{Bar graph\n| title = Carrier shares: January \u2013 December 2013<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\" />\n| bar_width   = 26\n| width_units = em\n| label_type  = Carrier&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| data_type   = Passengers (arriving and departing)\n|\n| label1   = [[Wright Air Service|Wright]]\n| data1    = 220\n| comment1 = 99.55%\n|\n| label2   = [[Tanana Air Service|Tanana]]\n| data2    = 1\n| comment2 = 0.45%\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Top domestic destinations: Jan. \u2013 Dec. 2013<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\">\n  {{cite web\n  | url = http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=LMA&End_YearMonth=24168\n  | title = Lake Minchumina, AK: Lake Minchumina Airport (LMA)\n  | publisher = [[Bureau of Transportation Statistics]] (BTS), [[Research and Innovative Technology Administration]] (RITA), [[U.S. Department of Transportation]]\n  | date = December 2013 | accessdate = June 25, 2014\n  }}\n</ref><!--NOTE: source does not list airlines associated with destinations at the time-->\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n! rowspan=\"2\" | City\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Airport name & IATA code\n! colspan=\"2\" | Passengers\n|-\n! 2013\n! 2012\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Fairbanks, Alaska]]\n| [[Fairbanks International Airport|Fairbanks International (FAI)]]\n| align=\"right\" | 100\n| align=\"right\" | 90\n|-\n| 2\n| [[McGrath, AK]]\n| [[McGrath Airport|McGrath Airport (MCG)]]\n| align=\"right\" | &lt;10\n| align=\"right\" | &lt;10\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Other sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* Essential Air Service documents ([http://www.regulations.gov/#!docketDetail;D=DOT-OST-2008-0237 Docket DOT-OST-2008-0237]) from the [[U.S. 